sweetened beverages.\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2441, \"end\": 2466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Health_Organization\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.730571678647164e-35, \"text\": \"World Health Organization\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Health_Organization\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Health_Organization\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"countries\", \"from\": 2482, \"to\": 2491}, {\"ngram\": \"tax sugar-sweetened beverages\", \"from\": 2495, \"to\": 2524}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A petition launched ahead of the Games called \\\"Kick Big Soda Out of Sport\\\" has more than 109,000 signatures, and been backed by a range of public health organisations including the World Obesity Federation.\", \"from\": 2527, \"to\": 2733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2708, \"end\": 2732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Obesity_Day\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"World Obesity Federation\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Obesity_Day\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Obesity_Day\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A petition\", \"from\": 2527, \"to\": 2537}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2556, \"to\": 2565}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Kick Big Soda\", \"from\": 2573, \"to\": 2587}, {\"ngram\": \"Sport\", \"from\": 2595, \"to\": 2600}, {\"ngram\": \"more than 109,000 signatures\", \"from\": 2606, \"to\": 2634}, {\"ngram\": \"a range\", \"from\": 2655, \"to\": 2662}, {\"ngram\": \"public health organisations\", \"from\": 2666, \"to\": 2693}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Environmental NGOs have also criticised the amount of plastic used to serve drinks at the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 2735, \"to\": 2837, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Environmental NGOs\", \"from\": 2735, \"to\": 2753}, {\"ngram\": \"the amount\", \"from\": 2775, \"to\": 2785}, {\"ngram\": \"plastic\", \"from\": 2789, \"to\": 2796}, {\"ngram\": \"drinks\", \"from\": 2811, \"to\": 2817}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 2821, \"to\": 2836}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Coca-Cola Company in May said nearly 10 out of 18 million refreshments served at the Olympics would be \\\"without single-use plastic\\\".\", \"from\": 2839, \"to\": 2975, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2839, \"end\": 2860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"score\": 0.9823384675164815, \"rank\": 0.01797907041984462, \"text\": \"The Coca-Cola Company\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"May\", \"from\": 2864, \"to\": 2867}, {\"ngram\": \"18 million refreshments\", \"from\": 2890, \"to\": 2913}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2924, \"to\": 2936}, {\"ngram\": \"single-use plastic\", \"from\": 2955, \"to\": 2973}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fanta, Sprite and Coca-Cola bottles have been served into reusable cups at Olympic venues, a practice some say runs counter to the Games' pledge to be the greenest in history.\", \"from\": 2977, \"to\": 3152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2977, \"end\": 2982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fanta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fanta\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fanta\"}, {\"begin\": 2995, \"end\": 3004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"score\": 0.999996060992571, \"rank\": 3.939022948203295e-06, \"text\": \"Coca-Cola\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coca-Cola\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Sprite\", \"from\": 2984, \"to\": 2990}, {\"ngram\": \"reusable cups\", \"from\": 3035, \"to\": 3048}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic venues\", \"from\": 3052, \"to\": 3066}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games' pledge\", \"from\"